   There's a cat on the loose on Long Island,
but it's best not to set out saucers of milk, authorities said.
   It may be a cougar.
   The animal left pawprints 4{ inches wide Tuesday in a wooded area
of Bellport, where it was spotted by two people, including a deputy
sheriff.
   They described it as a cat-like animal on the run.
   Linda Pew, supervisor of the Brookhaven Animal Shelter, said the
cat may be a runaway cougar kept as a pet.
   ``We think it was probably domesticated,'' said Pew.
