<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 380-38 roll call by which the House
approved a bill to impose criminal penalties for flag burning. The
bill is designed to overcome a Supreme Court decision which said
flag burning was a protected form of free speech.
   A ``yes'' vote is a vote to approve the bill.
   Voting yes were 229 Democrats and 151 Republicans.
   Voting no were 17 Democrats and 21 Republicans.
   X denotes those not voting.
   Present denotes those who voted they were ``present'' at the time
of the vote but did not vote ``yes'' or ``no'' on the issue.
   There are four vacancies in the 435-member House.
