<HEAD>Seek Probe Into Iowa Blast</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ohio Sen. John Glenn and Rep. Mary Rose Oakar
want Congress to look into the Navy's probe of the blast that killed
47 sailors on the USS Iowa.
   After separate briefings Tuesday by Rear Adm. Richard D.
Milligan, who directed the Navy's investigation, Oakar, D-Ohio, said
she was concerned about the ``reputations and families'' of the Iowa
sailors and Glenn, D-Ohio, said, he wanted to make sure such an
explosion wouldn't happen again.
   The Pentagon released a report last week that said
``circumstantial evidence'' indicated gunner's mate Clayton Hartwig
of Cleveland intentionally sparked the April 19 explosion on the
battleship.
   The report called Hartwig the ``principal suspect'' but said it
would be impossible to prove guilose nearby died in
the blast.
