<HEAD>Lauder Paid $350 for Each Vote</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Primary Rdp, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   If you are one of that rare breed, the New York
City Republican, and you're a member of that even rarer sub-species
that voted for Ronald Lauder for mayor, your vote was not worthless.
   It was worth $352 and change.
   The heir to the Estee Lauder cosmetics fortune spent about $13
million in the city's Republican primary, most of it his own money
and most of it negative TV advertising aimed at Rudolph Giuliani.
Giuliani thrashed him by a more than 2-to-1 margin.
   But Lauder did receive 36,905 votes in Tuesday's primary. If
Lauder spent exactly $13 million _ the bills are still coming in _
that averages out to $352.26 for every man and woman who voted for
him.
</TEXT>
