<SECOND>AM-Boat People,0150</SECOND>
<HEAD>53 Boat People Arrested in Connection With Island Riot</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police arrested 53 Vietnamese boat people
suspected of robbery, rape and other crimes during unrest on the
island where they had been housed, authorities said Wednesday.
   The arrested Vietnamese were among about 5,000 boat people placed
on Tai A Chau island after sailing into this British colony seeking
refuge from their Communist homeland.
   Violence on the island broke out last month. When police arrived,
they said about 1,000 Vietnamese threw stones at them. The police
fired tear gas to disperse the mob and then left the island.
   Senior police official Gregory Lam told local radio that 17 cases
of rape were reported during the island disturbance. Eight people
were arrested in connection with 12 of the cases, he said.
   Tai A Chau was evacuated earlier this month after a cholera
outbreak.
