<FIRST>r i AM-Brazil-BusCrash     09-13 0177</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Brazil-Bus Crash,0179</SECOND>
<UNK>30 Dead in Bus Accident in Brazil</UNK>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A crowded bus rammed into a truck
and caught fire Wednesday after the bus driver fell asleep at the
wheel, killing 30 people and injuring 14, a police spokeswoman said.
   Eunice Castro, a police official in the city of Belo Horizonte,
told The Associated Press the bus hit the back of the truck, went
into a ditch and burst into flames.
   ``It's a miracle anyone survived,'' she said in a telephone
interview. She said the bus was carrying 48 passengers from the
northeastern city of Bom Jesus da Lapa to Sao Paulo when the
accident occurred near Itatiaiucu, about 250 miles northwest of Rio.
   She said some of the injured were in serious condition.
   The truck's driver, Jose Batista da Silva, said in a television
interview that the bus was traveling about 62 mph. The speed limit
in Brazil is 50 mph.
   Ms. Castro said survivors reported that the bus driver fell
asleep at the wheel seconds before the accident.
</TEXT>
