<HEAD>Store Owner Stuck With 300 Lame-Duck Masks</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Koch, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mayor Edward I. Koch will be out of office by the
end of the year, but Paul Blum is afraid the mayor will be hanging
around his store a lot longer.
   Blum, owner of a costume and novelty shop in Greenwich Village,
slashed the price of a Koch mask to $1 Wednesday, hoping to sell his
