<HEAD>Cuban Train Derailment Injures Eight</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A train bound for Havana jumped the rails
Wednesday, injuring eight passengers, the Cuban government news
agency said.
   Prensa Latina, monitored in Mexico City, said the train was
traveling from the western province of Pinar del Rio to the Cuban
capital.
   The report quoted Cuban Interior Ministry official Jose Rene
Rocubert as saying one passenger was seriously hurt.
   The dispatch gave no reason for the derailment and did not say
exactly where it occurred.
   Prensa Latin said two train accidents last month killed a total
of 52 people and injured more than 300.
