<FIRST>d f BC-Britain-Bond     09-13 0137</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Bond,0143</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bond Corp. Sells Lonrho Stake</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bond Corp. Holdings Ltd., the beleaguered
Australian group led by Alan Bond, said Wednesday it sold its 20.4
percent stake in the British conglomerate Lonrho PLC, for an
undisclosed sum.
   Bond Corp. said it sold about 114.3 million shares to the British
investment firms Barclays de Zoete Wedd Securities Ltd. and Smith
New Court Securities PLC, for ``onward distribution to investors.''
   Lonrho stock was down the equivalent of 17 cents to $4.56 a share
at midafternoon on London's Stock Exchange.
   Bond Corp. bought its holding in Lonrho shares last autumn, which
prompted speculation of an impending bid.
   But Bond announced that he would sell his Lonrho holding at a
minimum price of $5.97 a share after Lonrho rejected Bond's offer to
cooperate with the British company.
</TEXT>
