<HEAD>Mobil to Realize $192 Million Gain on Exchange of Leases in Hong
Kong</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mobil Corp. said Wednesday it would earn $192
million on the exchange of property leases with the government of
Hong Kong.
   The gain would be reflected in the oil company's third-quarter
results, Mobil said.
   The company said in a statement its affiliate, Mobil Oil Hong
Kong, had exchanged the lease for its current terminal in Hong Kong
for a new lease on a site a mile away and the $192 million.
   Mobil said it planned to build a terminal on the new site with
twice the capacity of the existing facility.
