<SECOND>AM-S&amp;L Appointments,0149</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Appointments to Resolution Funding Corp.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two members were appointed Wednesday to the
Resolution Funding Corp., completing the makeup of the agency
created by the new savings and loan law to issue $30 billion in
bonds to fund the cleanup of insolvent thrifts.
   Treasury Secretary Nicholas F. Brady, chairman of the new
Resolution Trust Corp. Oversight Board, announced the appointments
of Brian D. Dittenhafer and Ronald R. Morphew as directors of the
corporation.
   Dittenhafer, president of the Federal Home Loan Bank of New York,
was appointed to a three-year term and designated chairman. Morphew,
president of the Federal Home Loan Bank of Indianapolis, was named
to a two-year term.
   Under the new S&amp;L law, the third member of the corporation is the
director of the Office of Finance of the Federal Home Loan Bank,
Austin C. Dowling.
</TEXT>
