<FILEID>AP-NR-09-13-89 2229EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-ABC-Magazine     09-13 0181</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-ABC-Magazine,0188</SECOND>
<HEAD>ABC Television Network Plans Bimonthly Magazines on Its Soap Operas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The ABC Television Network said Wednesday it
plans to launch a bimonthly magazine, Episodes, in February that
will be devoted to its own daytime soap operas.
   The magazine is the first of its kind for the television network,
a Capital Cities-ABC Inc. operation that said it has been developing
the publication for two years.
   Network officials said the purpose of the magazine is to attract
viewers to its daytime serials and to offer advertisers on those
shows another way to market their products.
   ABC said more than 18 million women watch its soap operas for at
least two hours a week, and that it hopes the magazine will have an
initial circulation of 2 million.
   The magazine will be available by telephone subscription. Those
wishing to subscribe will be directed in a promotional campaign that
will be carried on the ABC network starting in December to call a
900 number to sign up. The charge for the call and six issues will
be $3.
</TEXT>
